BT935 Analysis

BT935 - Shannon Diversity

cols <- grep("BT935",names(s),value=T);
grps <- factor(gsub("BT935_|_R[1234]$","",cols),levels=c("INVITRO_P0","INVITRO_CON","INVITRO_R","INVIVO_P0","ENG","MRD_CON","MRD_R","MRD_T","MRD_TR","REC_CON","REC_R","REC_T","REC_TR","CON_RETRANS_P0","CON_RETRANS_CON","CON_RETRANS_TR"));
sums <- apply( co.2[,cols] > 0,2,sum );
maxes <- apply( co.2[,cols],2,max );

df <- data.frame( Diversity=s[cols],Groups=grps,Sums=sums,MaxCloneSize=maxes );

ggplot( df, aes(x=Groups,y=Diversity)) + 
  geom_boxplot( colour="black" ) +
  geom_jitter( colour="red", height=0, width=0.20 ) +
  theme_pubr() +
  labs( title="BT935 Shannon Diversity Index" ) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1));

Plot BC size by rank??

l <- list();
for (grp in unique(grps)) {
  
  if (sum( grps == grp ) < 2) next;
  tmp <- as.data.frame(apply( co.2[,cols[ grps == grp ]],2,sort,decreasing=T ));
  colnames(tmp) <- gsub(".+_(R[0-4]+)$","\\1",colnames(tmp));
  tmp2 <- gather( tmp, key="Replicate",value="Fraction" ) %>% 
    filter( Fraction > 0 ) %>% 
    group_by( Replicate ) %>% 
    mutate(Rank=rank(desc(Fraction)));

  l[[grp]] <- tmp2 %>% ggplot( aes( x=Rank,y=Fraction,color=Replicate )) +
    geom_line() +
    geom_point() +
    scale_y_log10( name="Fraction of Population", limits=c(min(tmp2$Fraction),1)) +
    scale_x_log10( name="Clone Rank") +
    labs( title=grp, color="" ) +
    theme_pubr( legend=c(0.8,0.8) );
  
}

Prepare line plots for BT935

l2 <- list();
newGrps <- list();
newGrps[["INVITRO"]] <- c("ENG","INVIVO_P0");
newGrps[["MRD"]] <- c("MRD_CON","MRD_TR");
newGrps[["REC"]] <- c("REC_CON","REC_TR");

for (grpL in names(newGrps)) {

  if (sum( grps == grp ) < 2) next;
  tmp <- as.data.frame(apply( co.2[,cols[ grps %in% newGrps[[grpL]]] ],2,sort,decreasing=T ));
  tmp2 <- gather( tmp, key="Replicate",value="Fraction" ) %>% filter( Fraction > 0 ) %>% 
    group_by( Replicate ) %>% mutate(CloneFreq=rank(desc(Fraction)));
  tmp2$Color <- sapply( tmp2$Replicate, function(x) grps[ which( cols == x )]);

  l2[[grpL]] <- tmp2 %>% ggplot( aes( x=log10(Fraction),y=CloneFreq,group=Replicate,color=Color )) +
      geom_line( lwd=1 ) +
      scale_y_log10( name="Clones ≥ \u0192" ) +
      xlim( NA, 0 ) + xlab("Clonal Frequency") + 
      labs( title="BT935",color="Sample Group" ) +
      theme_pubr( legend=c(0.8,0.8) );
  
}

What these lineplots seem to show is the following:

BT935 - Recurrences

How to interpret these curves. It seems like, reproducibly, the Control populations are very much the same. Now, in the TMZ+Radiation tumours:
  • One replicate has become clonal, so looks like an outlier on the plot
  • Interestingly, the other two samples look pretty similar. The “background” population in the upper plateau, the slopes in the steepest part of the curves, the number of dominant clones, and finally the maximum clone size (~10%) all seem very similar between these two replicates. This was perhaps seen more effectively in the lineplots above.
